    "For these studies, a total of 5 531 turns (1 708 for neutral, 1 084 for sadness, 1 636 for happiness, and 1 103 for anger) were used[179].To evaluate the performance of semisupervised SER with 300, 600, 1 200, and 2400 labeled examples, the training set is used to randomly choose labeled instances, with an equal number of examples for each category.",
    "The remaining instances in the training set are known as unlabeled examples.",
    "Table 4 lists many comparison techniques that perform well on the IEMOCAP dataset, including two supervised approaches and four semisupervised learning methods.",
    "SVM and DNN are chosen as the foundational supervised techniques.",
    "DNN has a similar framework to the SSGAN, but it does not have an unsupervised loss."
